HEADWORD: Hypodermic syringe
<hw>Hyp`o*der"mic syr"inge</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>a small
syringe designed for use together with a <er>hypodermic needle{1}</er>
for injection of liquids directly under the skin, or into other parts of
the body of an animal.</def>⟦br⟧
